Webshims uses a very similiar API to extend jQuery properties. A pure idl attribute accessor implementation looks like this:
$.webshims.defineNodeNamesProperty('audio, video', 'currentTime', { 
    prop: { 
        get: function(){ 
            //your getter implementation ("this" refers to the element) 
        }, 
        set: function(value){
             //your setter implementation ("this" refers to the element) 
        } 
    } 
});
A content attribute implementation, which is reflected by an idl attribute:
$.webshims.defineNodeNamesProperty('input, textarea', 'placeholder', { 
    attr: { 
        get: function(){ 
            //your getter implementation ("this" refers to the element) 
        }, 
        set: function(value){
             //your setter implementation ("this" refers to the element) 
        } 
    },
    reflect: true, //true = default but there are different type for number, references to other elements, urls etc.
    initAttr: true // should the setter be invoked initially, if attribute is available
});
