. About the calls: They are not expensive, because webshims always uses simple selectors. Either just input or more specific input[type="date"] and so on. So they are pretty fast even in IE7. However, webshims currently does not always properly detect, wether an element already was "shim-med". So if you  call updatePolyfill multiple times on an element, which hasn't changed, it might lead to some other problems (events are bound twice and so on). I will open a ticket for this.
