. This actually is a jQuery mobile issue produced by the textinput widget. The best thing you can do: "Disable it." The main feature of the textinput widget is to wrap all input elements in a container. To be honest, I don't understand, that a libary for mobile devices is heavily altering the DOM only for layout issues. 
Here is a quick workaround, which has to run before domready/pagecreate whatever:
