1. Placeholder
   Technically it is possible, but it's not really my intention/suggestion. webshims feature are already balanced in filesize-/feature. And the placeholder is looked as a module of the form feature. The best way is to add a new polyfill, pointing to the old polyfill:
//add a new feature called formplaceholder
   $.webshims.addPolyfill('formplaceholder', {
           //point the implementation source to the standard placeholder-feature
           src: 'form-placeholder',
           //load this polyfill, if placeholder is not supported and the standard placeholder is not loaded
           test: function(list){
                return ($.inArray('form-placeholder', list) != -1 || Modernizr.input.placeholder);
           },
           //load dom-extend, if needed
           dependencies: ['dom-extend']
   });
   //load only placeholder with dependendcies
   $.webshims.polyfill('formplaceholder');
Note: The new polyfill 'formplaceholder' will still get his configuration from the 'forms-feature'. If you want to change the configuration for the placeholder. Currently only one config-option (use overlabel for all inputs), you have to set the options for the forms - feature:
$.webshims.setOptions('forms', {
    placeholderType: 'over'
});
