While datetime-local is now being shim, I'm noticing that after the user selects the date/time, the value is cleared. This is evident in the demo above, and in 1.11.0
. Upon farther review, I've found the culprit to be parseVal in form-number-date-ui.js.
In my locale, splitting on whitespace characters will result 3 parts, not two: date, time and meridian. Since it's not parsed back to a valid normalized local date and time string, the browser doesn't set the value.
I fixed it locally by adding the following branch, though I'm not sure it works for all locales:
javascript
} else if (fVal.length == 3) {
    val = this.date(fVal[0], o) +'T'+ this.time(fVal[1]+fVal[2], o);
}
. Want to weight in here, that having a second module loader, one we don't have control over, is an additional complexity for a problem we don't have: It would be much better for us to package the shims we would use, even if they aren't actually needed in each browser.
