Here's some code to replicate it:
```
<!doctype html>


Oh you little...






        .hiddenform-wrapper {
            display: none;
        }
        .hiddenform-wrapper.active {
            display: block;
        }
        input {
            width: 50%;
        }










Show form

    Modernizr.load([
            { load: 'js/jquery-1.10.2.min.js'},
            { 
                load: 'js/polyfiller.js',
                complete: function() {
                    //change webshims options
                    $.webshims.setOptions({
                        waitReady: false,
                        basePath: "js/shims/",
                        activeLang: 'sv'
                    });

                    //start polyfilling
                    $.webshims.polyfill('forms');

                    $('#showform').click(function() {
                        $('.hiddenform-wrapper').toggleClass('active');
                    });
                }
            }
        ]);



```
So I can avoid the bug by either removing display: none; while the shim is initializing (and put it back later), or if I don't set a procentual width to the input field. It's kind of annoying having to either though ;p
