. Current config : jQuery 1.8.3 and webshim 1.15.5
Found it ! 
It seems to be a edge case, related to jQuery and IE8.
In webshim.errorBox.create(), when trying to generate an errorbox using "span" : 
errorBox = $('<'+errorBoxWrapper+' class="'+ errorBoxClass +'" hidden="hidden" style="display: none;">');
sets errorBox to "undefined" in IE8.
Using the following syntax works (we have to explicitly close the tag).
errorBox = $('<'+errorBoxWrapper+' class="'+ errorBoxClass +'" hidden="hidden" style="display: none;"></'+errorBoxWrapper+'>');
It only happens with "span", not other tags... Don't ask me why ^^
I will test the other syntaxes of explicit element creation in jQuery and make a PR.
